  "text": "The Apache Kafka Streams DSL (Domain Specific Language) is a high-level abstraction built on top of the Processor API. The migration path from DSL to Processor API involves understanding how each DSL operation maps to its underlying processor implementation.\n\n## Key DSL to Processor API Mappings\n\n### KStream Operations\n\n**map() operation** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/KStreamImpl.java):\nThe KStreamImpl.map() method at lines 283-311 creates a KStreamMap processor supplier. KStreamMap (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/KStreamMap.java) implements ProcessorSupplier and returns a KStreamMapProcessor that extends ContextualProcessor. This processor transforms both keys and values using a KeyValueMapper function and forwards modified records.\n\n**filter() operation** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/KStreamImpl.java, lines 146-172):\nThe KStreamImpl.filter() method creates a KStreamFilter processor supplier. KStreamFilter (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/KStreamFilter.java) implements FixedKeyProcessorSupplier and returns a KStreamFilterProcessor extending ContextualFixedKeyProcessor. It evaluates a Predicate and only forwards records that match the predicate condition.\n\n**groupBy() operation** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/KStreamImpl.java, lines 698-715):\nThe KStreamImpl.groupBy() method returns a KGroupedStreamImpl instance (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/KGroupedStreamImpl.java). This class repartitions the stream by the new key selector and creates a grouped stream ready for aggregations.\n\n**mapValues() operation** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/KStreamMapValues.java):\nImplements FixedKeyProcessorSupplier, transforming only values while preserving keys. Returns KStreamMapProcessor extending ContextualFixedKeyProcessor.\n\n**flatMap() operation** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/KStreamFlatMap.java):\nImplements ProcessorSupplier. The KStreamFlatMapProcessor extends ContextualProcessor and forwards multiple output records for each input record.\n\n**flatMapValues() operation** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/KStreamFlatMapValues.java):\nImplements FixedKeyProcessorSupplier. Expands values into multiple records while preserving keys.\n\n**peek() operation** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/KStreamPeek.java):\nImplements FixedKeyProcessorSupplier. The KStreamPeekProcessor executes a ForeachAction for side effects and forwards unmodified records.\n\n**split/branch() operation** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/KStreamBranch.java):\nImplements ProcessorSupplier. Routes records to different child processors based on predicate evaluation.\n\n### KGroupedStream Operations (Aggregations)\n\n**aggregate() operation** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/KGroupedStreamImpl.java, lines 110-140):\nUses KStreamAggregate (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/KStreamAggregate.java) which implements KStreamAggProcessorSupplier. The KStreamAggregateProcessor extends ContextualProcessor and maintains state in a key-value store, applying an Initializer and Aggregator function to accumulate values by key.\n\n**reduce() operation** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/KGroupedStreamImpl.java, lines 71-106):\nUses KStreamReduce (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/KStreamReduce.java) implementing KStreamAggProcessorSupplier. Similar to aggregate but uses a Reducer function instead, maintaining state in a key-value store.\n\n### KTable Operations\n\n**filter() operation on KTable** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/KTableFilter.java):\nImplements KTableProcessorSupplier. The processor evaluates a Predicate and outputs null values (tombstones) for records that don't match, enabling change tracking in the table.\n\n**mapValues() operation on KTable** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/kstream/internals/KTableMapValues.java):\nImplements KTableProcessorSupplier. Transforms values while maintaining keys and tracking value changes.\n\n## Processor API Base Classes\n\n**ProcessorSupplier** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/api/ProcessorSupplier.java):\nFactory interface for creating Processor instances. Used for operations that can change both keys and values.\n\n**FixedKeyProcessorSupplier** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/api/FixedKeyProcessorSupplier.java):\nFactory interface for creating FixedKeyProcessor instances. Used for operations that preserve keys.\n\n**ContextualProcessor** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/api/ContextualProcessor.java):\nBase class for processors that change keys/values. Provides access to ProcessorContext for forwarding records and managing state.\n\n**ContextualFixedKeyProcessor** (sg-evals/kafka--0753c489:streams/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/streams/processor/api/ContextualFixedKeyProcessor.java):\nBase class for processors with fixed keys. Provides access to FixedKeyProcessorContext.\n\n## Migration Strategy\n\nWhen migrating from DSL to Processor API for custom state store management:\n\n1. Replace KStream.map() with a custom ProcessorSupplier and ContextualProcessor implementation\n2. Replace KStream.filter() with a custom FixedKeyProcessorSupplier and ContextualFixedKeyProcessor implementation  \n3. Replace groupBy().aggregate() with a custom processor that manages state store directly via StateStore APIs\n4. Use StateStoreContext methods (getStateStore) to access custom stores instead of relying on automatic state management\n5. Implement StoreSupplier to provide custom KeyValueStore implementations with specialized behavior\n\nThe Processor API provides lower-level control over state management, topology building, and record processing, making it suitable for advanced use cases requiring custom state store implementations, special store types, or fine-grained control over processing semantics."
